  "analysis": "The template analysis shows the structure with placeholders and a conditional section. Key observations: 1) Placeholders are consistently formatted as {{PLACEHOLDER}}. 2) The relocation section is properly marked with {{IF_RELOCATION}}...{{END_IF_RELOCATION}}. 3) All necessary data fields are present in the employee_data.json. The script will need to: 1) Load the template, 2) Replace all placeholders with data, 3) Handle the relocation conditional section based on RELOCATION_PACKAGE value, 4) Save the result to /root/offer_letter_filled.docx.",
  "plan": "1) Load the template using python-docx, 2) Read employee_data.json, 3) Create a function to replace placeholders, 4) Create a function to handle conditional sections, 5) Process the document, 6) Save to the target file. I'll implement this in a Python script and execute it.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 << 'EOF'
import json
from docx import Document
from docx.oxml import CT_P, CT_T
from docx.oxml.ns import qn

# Load template
doc = Document('offer_letter_template.docx')

# Load employee data
with open('employee_data.json') as f:
    data = json.load(f)

# Function to replace placeholders
for para in doc.paragraphs:
    for key, value in data.items():
        placeholder = f'{{{{{key}}}}}'
        if placeholder in para.text:
            para.text = para.text.replace(placeholder, str(value))

# Function to handle conditional sections
for table in doc.tables:
    for row in table.rows:
        for cell in row.cells:
            for para in cell.paragraphs:
                if '{{IF_RELOCATION}}' in para.text:
                    if data.get('RELOCATION_PACKAGE', '').upper() == 'YES':
                        # Keep the content
                        para.text = para.text.replace('{{IF_RELOCATION}}', '').replace('{{END_IF_RELOCATION}}', '')
                    else:
                        # Remove the content
                        para.text = ''

# Save the document
doc.save('/root/offer_letter_filled.docx')
EOF
